Name: Great Bagel
Description: This is my favorite bagel place in Lexington! It's the best and I get a bacon, egg, and cheese bagel.

Name: Rupp Arena
Description: This is the basketball arena where UK plays. I have been going to the games forever and it is a really special place.

Name: Chevy Chase
Type: This is the area my friends and I live in. There are shops, restaurants, and cute neighborhoods in this area.

Name: Drake's Restaurant
Description: This restaurant has everything and is a Lexington staple. My best friends family owns the restuarant, so it makes it very special.

Name: Ashland Park
Description: This is a park in chevy chase. It is great to walk around and has beautiful trees and greenery.

Name: Graeter's Ice Cream
Description: A classic ice cream stop known for its famous Black Raspberry Chip flavor. This place is nostalgic and one of my favorites!

Name: County Club
Description: This is a hole in the wall restaurant. The food is very good and the menu changes a lot, so you can always try something new.

Name: Keeneland
Description: Keenenald is one of the reasons people travel to Lexington. It is a place to horse bet, watch the races, and have fun with friends.

Name: Kroger Field
Description: Home of University of Kentucky football and a major gathering place on game days. The stadium is very important to Kentucky fans.

Name: Old Kentucky Chocolates
Description: My favorite chocolate shop in Lexington! They have candy bars and chocolate covored grapes that are a must!
